label: Digital Specimen
definition: A digital representation of a physical specimen, following the concept of the FAIR Digital Object (FDO). Each physical specimen that has been administrated as a separate entity will be a Digital Specimen.

label: ID
definition: The unique identifier of the object

label: Version
definition: The version of the object, each change generates a new version

label: Status
definition: The status of the Digital Object

label: Modified
definition: The timestamp that the object was last changed, which resulted in a new version of the object

label: Created
definition: The timestamp that the object was created in DiSSCo

label: Type
definition: The DOI to the FDO type of the object

label: MIDS Level
definition: The MIDS level of the object, see https://www.tdwg.org/community/cd/mids/

label: Normalised Physical Specimen ID
definition: The physical specimen identifier of the object. When locally unique this is a combination between source-system-id and the local identifier

label: Physical Specimen ID
definition: The physical specimen identifier of the object. Taken over as-is

label: Physical Specimen ID Type
definition: To indicate if the physical identifier is globally unique or locally unique

label: Topic Origin
definition: The topic origin of the specimen

label: Topic Domain
definition: The topic domain of the specimen
enum: Life, Environment, Earth System, Extraterrestrial, Cultural Artefacts, Archive Material, Unclassified

label: Topic Discipline
definition: The topic discipline of the specimen
enum: Anthropology, Botany, Astrogeology, Geology, Microbiology, Palaeontology, Zoology, Ecology, Other Biodiversity, Other Geodiversity, Unclassified

label: Is Marked As Type
definition: The specimen is marked as a type specimen

label: Is Known To Contain Media
definition: Indicates if there are any media objects attached to this specimen

label: Specimen Name
definition: The accepted specimen name of the digital specimen

label: Source System ID
definition: The handle to the source system object which retrieved the data from the CMS

label: Source System Name
definition: The name of the source system as provided to DiSSCo

label: Living Or Preserved
definition: Whether the specimen is living or preserved

label: Language
definition: The language of the Digital Specimen metadata. Only indicate, not enforced. Recommended to use ISO 639-1 codes

label: Organisation ID
definition: ROR or Wikidata identifier of the organisation

label: Organisation Name
definition: Full museum name according to ROR or Wikidata

label: Information Withheld
examples: location information not given for endangered species

label: Data Generalizations
examples: Coordinates generalized from original GPS coordinates to the nearest half degree grid cell.

label: Owner Organisation Code
definition: The name used by the organisation having ownership of the object

label: Rights Holder
examples: Museu de História Natural e da Ciência da Universidade do Porto

label: Verbatim Label
examples:
ILL: Union Co. Wolf Lake by Powder Plant Bridge. 1 March 1975 Coll. S. Ketzler, S. Herbert

Monotoma longicollis 4 ♂ Det TC McElrath 2018

INHS Insect Collection 456782

label: Organism Remarks
examples: One of a litter of six

label: Has Material Entity
definition: Contains zero or more ods:MaterialEntity objects

label: Has Identification
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identification objects

label: Has Assertion
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Assertion objects

label: Has Event
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Event objects

label: Has Entity Relationship
definition: Contains zero or more ods:EntityRelationship objects

label: Has Citation
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Citation objects

label: Has Identifier
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identifier objects

label: Has Chronometric Age
definition: Contains zero or more ods:ChronometricAge objects

label: Has Agent
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Agent objects

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: Object containing the tombstone metadata of the object. Only present when ods:status is ods:Tombstone

label: Material Entity
definition: Contains the information about the Material object attached to the Digital Specimen. The array will always have one MaterialEntity object of type `ods:Specimen` which is the main MaterialEntity object of the Digital Specimen. It can have additional MaterialEntities which will then be a `ods:SpecimenPart`

label: Organisation ID
definition: ROR or Wikidata identifier of the organisation

label: Organisation Name
definition: Full museum name according to ROR or Wikidata

label: Owner Organisation Code
definition: The name used by the organisation having ownership of the object

label: Verbatim Label
examples:
ILL: Union Co. Wolf Lake by Powder Plant Bridge. 1 March 1975 Coll. S. Ketzler, S. Herbert

Monotoma longicollis 4 ♂ Det TC McElrath 2018

INHS Insect Collection 456782

label: Has Identification
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identification objects

label: Has Assertion
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Assertion objects

label: Has Entity Relationship
definition: Contains zero or more ods:EntityRelationship objects

label: Has Citation
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Citation objects

label: Has Identifier
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identifier objects

label: Has Event
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Event objects

label: Has Agent
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Agent objects

label: Identification
definition: A generic identification class, containing information about who and when the identification was made, including the status of the identification.

label: Taxon Formula
definition: The full formula of the taxonomic identification

label: Identification References
examples: Aves del Noroeste Patagonico. Christie et al. 2004.

label: Is Verified Identification
definition: If this is the accepted identification, based on https://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/identificationVerificationStatus

label: Identification Remarks
examples: Distinguished between Anthus correndera and Anthus hellmayri based on the comparative lengths of the uñas.

label: Has Citation
definition: Can contain zero to more ods:Citation objects

label: Has Taxon Identification
definition: Can contain zero to more ods:TaxonIdentification objects

label: Taxon Identification
definition: A taxonomic determination, containing the full taxonomic tree of the identification.

label: Scientific Name HTML Label
definition: A Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML) representation of the scientific name. Includes correct formatting of the name.

label: Taxon Source
definition: The source of the taxonomic concept

label: Taxon Remarks
examples: this name is a misspelling in common use

label: Vernacular Name
examples: Meerval | Wels | Catfish | Silure glane | Wels | Waller | Siluro | Malle

label: Event
definition: A generic event class containing information about a particular activity at a certain place an time. An example is the collecting event.

label: Protocol Descriptions
examples: Three conventional harp traps (3.2m ht x 2.2m w) were established in flight path zones for a period of 4 hrs at dawn and dusk for a total of 10 trap nights. Traps were visited on an hourly basis during each deployment period and the trap catch recorded for species, size, weight, sex, age and maternal status.

label: Field Notes
examples: Notes available in the Grinnell-Miller Library

label: Event Remarks
examples: After the recent rains the river is nearly at flood stage

label: Collector Name
definition: The full name of the collector

label: Collector ID
definition: The identifier of the collector, recommended would be a ORCID or Wikidata ID

label: Has Assertion
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Assertion objects

label: Location
definition: Contains an object of type ods:Location

label: Location
definition: A generic location class containing information about a where a specific event took place.

label: Verbatim Locality
examples: 25 km NNE Bariloche por R. Nac. 237

label: Minimum Distance Above Surface In Meters
Maximum Distance Above Surface In Meters
Geo Reference
definition: An object which describes the geographical reference of the location of the specimen.

label: Geological Context
definition: An object which describes the geological context of th location of the specimen.

label: Agent
definition: A generic agent class, containing information about the actor who performed an activity. This could be a person, an organization or a machine.

label: Role Name
definition: Indicates the role of the agent, https://schema.org/roleName

label: Start Date
definition: Date the agent began the role

label: End Date
definition: Date the agent ended the role

label: Role Order
definition: Order of the agent in the role. Can be used to indicate the order of importance

label: Email
definition: Email of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: URL
definition: URL of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: Has Identifier
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identifier objects

label: Assertion
definition: A generic assertion class, containing information about a statement that is made about a digital object. An example is the measurement of the leaf or the wingspan of a specimen.

label: Measurement Accuracy
examples: 0.1, normal distribution with variation of 2 m

label: Assertion By Agent
definition: The agent who made the assertion, contains an ods:Agent object

label: Assertion Protocol
definition: The protocol used to make the assertion

label: Assertion Protocol ID
definition: The ID of the protocol used to make the assertion

label: Citation
definition: A generic class containing the information about a citation in which the Digital Object is mentioned or which had influence on the Digital Object.

label: Citation Remarks
definition: Any further remarks about the citation

label: Reference Year
definition: The year the reference was published

label: Reference Iri
definition: Reference to the web source of this citation

label: Entity Relationship
definition: Describes relationships between digital object and any external resources. An example could be a relationship to the Sequence record of the specimen in a DNA database.

label: Related Resource URI
definition: The URI of the related resource

label: Entity Relationship Order
definition: When multiple relationships are added an order can be defined

label: Relationship According To Agent
definition: The agent who created the entity relationship. Contains an ods:Agent object

label: Relationship Remarks
examples: Mother and offspring collected from the same nest

label: Identifier
definition: A generic Identifier class which can be attached to multiple classes. It captures information about any identifier of the class.

label: Title
definition: The type of the identifier, https://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title

label: Local Title
definition: The local title of the identifier

label: Identifier
definition: The value for the identifier, https://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier

label: Format
definition: Mime type of content returned by identifier in case the identifier is resolvable. https://purl.org/dc/terms/format

label: Is Part Of Label
definition: Indicates whether the identifier is part of the physical label

label: Is Barcode Or NFC
definition: Indicates whether the identifier is part of the barcode or nfc chip

label: Is ID Persistent
definition: Indicates whether the identifier is a persistent identifier

label: Chronometric Age
definition: An approximation of a temporal position (in the sense conveyed by https://www.w3.org/TR/owl-time/#time:TemporalPosition) that is supported via evidence.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age Protocol
definition: The verbatim name of the protocol used to determine the chronometric age.

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: The tombstone metadata about the tombstoned digital object, including the what, who and when of the tombstoning.

label: Tombstone Date
definition: Timestamp the Digital Object was tombstoned and no longer active.

label: Tombstone Text
definition: A reason why the Digital Object was tombstoned
examples: This is a duplicate of XXX, This object was made by mistake

label: Tombstoned By Agent
definition: The agent who tombstoned the object, contains an ods:Agent object

label: Has Related Pid
definition: The PIDs of the object the tombstoned object is related to
